abilities.effect:
You can sense the approximate location of nearby metal, although other elements (especially wood) may disrupt this sense. This effect is heightened if you concentrate.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You can sense the approximate location of nearby wood and plants, although other elements (especially metal) may disrupt this sense. This effect is heightened if you concentrate.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You can sense how air nearby is moving, and can easily find drafts and odd air movement. This effect is heightened if you concentrate.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You have a basic control of lightning that allows you to shield yourself from static shocks and create small flashes of lightning.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You may clumsily move and control a single nearby wooden object that you could hold in one hand.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You may clumsily move and control a single nearby metal object that you could hold in one hand.
&nbsp;
This does not typically provide die on Skill Challenges or Interactions, but may allow you to attempt things that would otherwise be impossible.

You can modify the physical properties of metal to a moderate degree, allowing you to make iron as hard as steel or the reverse. For maximum effect you must be touching the metal. The effect persists for a short time after you stop touching it. You may affect more mild change from a short distance. Finally, you can work metal with your touch with the same precision and speed as if you had metalworking tools (but not a forge) and you do not need _Smith's Tools_ to repair metal equipment.
&nbsp;
When using this aspect of your craft, gain +1 die on Skill Challenges and Interactions.

You can effortlessly create powerful bursts of wind, capable of pushing people back and launching small objects. In addition, you can control and manipulate the wind, creating specific drafts and movement of the air, allowing you to clumsily manipulate small objects from a distance or precisely manipulating powdery substances and the like.
&nbsp;
When using this aspect of your craft, gain +1 die on Skill Challenges and Interactions.

You can manipulate living plant matter, encouraging growth and changing its shape. If you do this over an extended period these changes are permanent, and can result in otherwise impossible growth. Rapid forced growth and manipulation tends to stress the plants, and the spirits in the plant will force it to return to its original state after a short time. In general, you can quickly form vine-like structures from grass and other small plantlife and given time can form more intricate and complex flora. You can accomplish this at a short distance, but the effect is enhanced if you are touching the plant.
&nbsp;
When using this aspect of your craft, gain +1 die on Skill Challenges and Interactions.

You are a skilled artist and, regardless of your specialty, are skilled at drawing and sketching. Given appropriate tools you can faithfully reproduce images of things seen on your adventures, and excel at understanding complex imagery and how a piece of art was made, which could grant additional insight. Additionally, choose a specialty for your art such as painting or sculpture. When working on or analyzing anything that matches your specialty all of these effects are heightened. Finally, you always understand the meaning an artist was attempting to represent when seeing their art, even if that is not how you feel about it.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as an artist would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You have studied herbs, and can identify most herbs at a glance. For those that you cannot, you at least have a general sense of their properties, and can always tell if an herb would be toxic. In addition to being able to identify herbs, you are well-versed on their properties, where they grow, and other useful details.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as an herbalist would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are a skilled hunter, and have a deep knowledge of different animals, where they might live, and the best way to hunt them down. You know how to best prepare most animals found in the wild, and have a deep knowledge of the best ways to track various creatures.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as a hunter would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

Whenever you <u>Hunt</u> as a _Camp_ or _Travel_ _Action_ treat yourself as having placed an additional die on the _Advantage_. You may always look at your current area's **Hunting Chart** before deciding to roll on it, although the GM may hide the specifics of the rarest option on the table.
&nbsp;
Additionally, when you need to track something while traveling, you may spend &#9634; for that Augment.

You have an innate sense of the outdoors and, while you lack the specific knowledge that a specialist might, you can identify dangers at a glance, and have a general knowledge of the outdoors. You have broad knowledge of plants and animals, as well as common spirit dangers of the wilds.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as a ranger would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are used to long hours working in the forge, which has given you a strong back, endurance, and the ability to use a wide variety of heavy tools. Additionally, when seeing another smith's hands, tools, or forge you can get a sense of their skill level and personality. This ability works to a lesser extent when you see a piece of their handiwork.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as an blacksmith would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are well-versed in different types of metal, and can easily identify most metals and their properties at a glance. For those that you cannot, you at least have a general sense of their properties. Additionally, you have a deep understanding of metal craftsmanship, and can easily identify the strongest and weakest point on something made of metal.
&nbsp;
When your knowledge of metal would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are well-versed in different types of weapons, as well as how they are made. You intuitively understand the function, craftsmanship, and cultural significance of weapons, and can accurately assess the condition of a weapon at a glance. Additionally, from a weapon, you can gain insight into its maker and skill level of the wielder.
&nbsp;
When your background and skills as a weaponsmith would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction.

You are resilient against punishment and can push through effects that would stop lesser creatures in their track. You are resistant to pain, toxins, and other afflictions to a frightening degree and seem to have a never-ending pool of stamina.
&nbsp;
When your exceptional toughness would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction. Additionally, in these circumstances you may spend one &#9634; as if it were &#8863; or to play *Duration* if appropriate.

You have an innate quality about you that puts people at ease in your presence. Strangers warm to you quickly, are quick to offer a helping hand, and are more likely to share information with you.
&nbsp;
When your charm and ability to persuade would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction. Additionally, in these circumstances you may spend one &#9634; as if it were &#8863; or to play *Incitement* if appropriate.

You are fast and able to easily navigate the world around you. When their is a question of who gets somewhere first it is nearly always you, and you can easily navigate even difficult terrain.
&nbsp;
When your speed, agility, and general manueverability would aid in a situation, gain +1 die on an appropriate Skill Challenge or Interaction. Additionally, in these circumstances you may spend one &#9634; as if it were &#8863; or to play *Speed* if appropriate.
